✅ Requirements
A basic Freemarker setup (via Spring Boot or embedded server)

Modern web browser (no build tools needed)

🔧 To Run:
Clone this repository:

bash
Copy
Edit
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/employee-directory.git
Place the project inside your Freemarker-compatible web app or static server.

Open index.ftl in the browser (or access it via your web server).

All data is handled locally in-memory — no backend is needed.

🧩 Project Features
💻 Dashboard Page
Displays employee cards in a responsive grid layout.

Each card shows: Name, Email, Department, Role

Includes Edit and Delete buttons for each employee.

➕ Add/Edit Employee
A dynamic form (modal) with:

First Name, Last Name, Email, Department, Role

Validations for required fields and email format

Edit pre-fills the form.

Cancel closes the modal without saving.

🔍 Filter / Sort / Search
Filter sidebar:

Filter by First Name, Department, Role

Top bar:

Search by name or email (case-insensitive)

Sort dropdown by First Name or Department

📄 Pagination
Choose items per page: 10, 25, 50, 100

Dynamically renders page buttons

Reset on filtering, searching, or sorting

📱 Responsive Design
Fully responsive layout

Mobile-first design

Smooth layout scaling from mobile to desktop

